ent of the Bare Knuckle/Streets of Rage series which was followed by Streets of Rage 2 and Streets of Rage 3. The game was converted to Game Gear, Sega CD and Master System. In 2007, the game was released for the Wii's Virtual Console in North America and Europe, and in 2009 it was released for the iOS via the App Store. It was again made available as part of Sonic's Ultimate Genesis Collection in 2009 on both the PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360 consoles.", "themes": [{"id": 1, "name": "Action"}, {"id": 18, "name": "Science fiction"}], "url": "https://www.igdb.com/games/streets-of-rage", "videos": [{"id": 8161, "name": "Gameplay video", "video_id": "sLpS_s1PaXM", "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sLpS_s1PaXM", "title": "Streets of Rage Gameplay", "thumb": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sLpS_s1PaXM/hqdefault.jpg"}, {"id": 8162, "name": "Game intro", "video_id": "MXjaCkPWpvU", "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MXjaCkPWpvU", "title": "Streets of Rage Intro [High Quality]", "thumb": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MXjaCkPWpvU/hqdefault.jpg"}, {"id": 48559, "name": "Gameplay Video", "video_id": "F61gi5Tz1NA", "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F61gi5Tz1NA", "title": "Streets Of Rage (1991) [Sega Genesis] Complete Playthrough", "thumb": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/F61gi5Tz1NA/maxresdefault.jpg"}]}